They are failing because your tests still expect the **old behavior** (`500 Internal Server Error`), but you now want browser endpoints to redirect to your error UI.

The visible failing test is this one:

```java
startAuthentication_shouldThrowInternalServerError_whenAppIdMissing
```

It currently expects:

```java
.andExpect(status().isInternalServerError());
```

Change it to a redirect expectation.

First ensure the `try` starts **before** the appId validation in `startAuthentication()`. Otherwise the `IllegalArgumentException` escapes and the PF handler returns XML again.

```java
@GetMapping("/start")
public ResponseEntity<Void> startAuthentication(
        @RequestHeader(value = "APP_ID", required = false) String headerAppId,
        @RequestParam(value = "appId", required = false) String queryAppId,
        HttpServletRequest request) {

    try {
        String appId = headerAppId != null && !headerAppId.isBlank()
                ? headerAppId
                : queryAppId;

        if (appId == null || appId.isBlank()) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException(
                    "APP_ID header or appId query param is empty");
        }

        // keep your current duplicate-request and redirect logic here

    } catch (Exception exception) {
        log.error("Authentication start failed", exception);

        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.FOUND)
                .location(URI.create("/arthur-core/error/technical"))
                .build();
    }
}
```

Then replace that test with:

```java
@Test
void startAuthentication_shouldRedirectToTechnicalError_whenAppIdIsMissing()
